OL,6,FNicola said: "It's an affectionate
OL,7,Fstory about people in the autumn of
OL,8,Ftheir lives. The show is a life-
OL,9,Faffirming view of survivors; children
OL,10,Fof the Windrush generation. The
OL,11,FWindrush scandal and its attendant
OL,12,Fhypocrisy is laid bare in this show.
OL,14,F"The show exposes the unfair
OL,15,Fpredicament of people who having lived
OL,16,Fand worked in the UK for decades, are
OL,17,Fnow heartlessly being shown that they
OL,18,Fare undesirable."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/12
